cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with an extension of Propositional Dynamic Logic (PDL) and its expressiveness over different language classes. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the separation of PDLs over regular, visibly pushdown, and deterministic context-free languages using automata-theoretic techniques. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper introduces an extension of PDL that allows programs to be in a language of L rather than just regular. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) may be relevant as the paper discusses the use of automata-theoretic techniques to separate PDLs, which involves the manipulation of data structures such as pushdown automata. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) may be relevant as the paper discusses the expressiveness of PDL over different language classes, which can be related to computational complexity.
